      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a strong take. But isn't it kind of irresponsible to just keep borrowing money indefinitely? If the debt gets too high, doesn't that eventually hurt the very people you're trying to help through inflation or economic collapse? Or is paying it down just not a real priority at all?",
